  "body": "### Description\r\nAs an implementor, I want `BeaconStateUtil.get_shuffling` to work as designed in the spec, so that my client conforms to the beacon chain spec.\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* `BeaconStateUtil.get_shuffling` should work for all epoch input values, and should be bounds checked to verify IllegalArgumentExceptions are not thrown.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n1. Call `BeaconStateUtil.get_shuffling` with any long value smaller than 32 bits.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** `BeaconStateUtil.get_shuffling` works as described in the spec.\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** `BeaconStateUtil.get_shuffling` throws an IllegalArgumentException\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n`BeaconStateUtil.get_shuffling` attempts to wrap a minimized Bytes value in a Bytes32 which will only work if the minimized value is 32 bytes in length. This logic should be correct to work for all bytes values.\r\n",
